body:
The inliner is inlining all instances of a module with a non-local `InlineAnnotation`, irrespective of the current path.  I opened a similar issue for the Scala FIRRTL compiler here: https://github.com/chipsalliance/firrtl/issues/2498

```mlir
  firrtl.nla @nla [#hw.innerNameRef<@Top::@foo>, @Foo]
  firrtl.module @Foo() attributes {annotations = [{circt.nonlocal = @nla, class = "firrtl.passes.InlineAnnotation"}]} {
    %f = firrtl.wire  : !firrtl.uint<1>
  }
  firrtl.module @Top() {
    firrtl.instance foo sym @foo  {annotations = [{circt.nonlocal = @nla, class = "circt.nonlocal"}]} @Foo()
    firrtl.instance bar  @Foo()
  }
```
`circt-opt --pass-pipeline='firrtl.circuit(firrtl-inliner)' inline.mlir` produces:
```mlir
  firrtl.circuit "Top"  {
    firrtl.module @Top() {
      %foo_f = firrtl.wire  : !firrtl.uint<1>
      %bar_f = firrtl.wire  : !firrtl.uint<1>
    }
  }
  ```
